  5→//! JJK MCP Server - Single dispatcher tool for all jjx operations
  6→//!
  7→//! Exposes one MCP tool (`jjx`) that takes a command name and JSON params,
  8→//! then dispatches to the appropriate handler. This replaces 25 individual
  9→//! MCP tools with a single entry point, reducing ToolSearch friction.
 10→//!
 11→//! Handlers return (i32, String) — exit code and accumulated output.
 12→//! The MCP layer converts this to CallToolResult (success/error).
 13→
 14→use std::path::PathBuf;
